cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper is primarily focused on the management and control of data centers using predictive computational and executable models obtained through data-science tools. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). 

The paper also extensively uses data-science tools and techniques such as BigQuery and ensemble classifiers, indicating a strong presence of machine learning and data mining. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the practicality of including the predictive model as the central component of a data-driven autonomic manager, which involves control and decision-making in real-time. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
